EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Rules, Privileges and Elections
EventItemTitle: Resolution adding a new rule to the Rules of the Council.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York City charter, in relation to requiring that all proposed rules be reviewed by the law department and the mayor’s office of operations.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that all proposed rules be reviewed by the law department and the mayor’s office of operations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the electrical code, the repeal of section 27-3025 of the administrative code of the city of New York and the enactment of a new section 27-3025.
EventItemMatterName: In relation to the electrical code.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to firefighter applicants who have completed high school in the city.
EventItemMatterName: Firefighter applicants who have completed high school in the city.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to damages for delay clauses in public contracts.
EventItemMatterName: Public Contracts, Damages For Delay

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the repair of leaks occurring in certain portions of service pipes by the Department of Environmental Protection.
EventItemMatterName: Leak Repair Service Pipes

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Public Service Commission to include language in utility tariffs to prohibit the placement of utility meters in front of residential buildings throughout New York City.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Public Service Commission to include language in utility tariffs to prohibit the placement of utility meters in front of residential buildings throughout NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to notices of violation issued by the department of sanitation for illegal postings.
EventItemMatterName: Notices of violation issued by the department of sanitation for illegal postings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to training requirements for all persons engaged in any hoisting or lowering activity.
EventItemMatterName: Training requirements for all persons engaged in any hoisting or lowering activity.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to benefits pursuant to section four hundred twenty-one-a of the real property tax law.
EventItemMatterName: Benefits pursuant to section four hundred twenty-one-a of the real property tax law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to civil penalties for unlicensed plumbing and fire suppression work.
EventItemMatterName: Civil penalties for unlicensed plumbing and fire suppression work.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the operation of material hoists.
EventItemMatterName: Operation of material hoists.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to payment of notices of violation for parking violations at check cashing businesses.
EventItemMatterName: Payment of notices of violation for parking violations at check cashing businesses.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the implementation of technology to allow traffic enforcement agents to issue idling tickets through their hand-held computers.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the implementation of technology to allow traffic enforcement agents to issue idling tickets through their hand-held computers.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to carbon monoxide and smoke detecting devices.
EventItemMatterName: Carbon monoxide and smoke detecting devices.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter in relation to authorizing the Civilian Complaint Review Board to prosecute cases of police misconduct the board has substantiated.
EventItemMatterName: Authorizing the Civilian Complaint Review Board to prosecute cases of police misconduct the board has substantiated.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to bicycles offered for rental.
EventItemMatterName: Bicycles offered for rental.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Congress to approve a health care reform bill that will not restrict women's reproductive health or burden their right to choose by forcing women to seek alternative or supplemental insurance to obtain an abortion.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to approve a health care reform bill that will not restrict women's reproductive health or burden their right to choose by forcing women to seek alternative or supplemental insurance to obtain an abortion.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to streamlining approvals for environmentally beneficial  technologies, design and construction techniques, materials and products.
EventItemMatterName: Streamlining approvals for environmentally beneficial technologies, design and construction techniques, materials and products.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring city plantings to be stormwater tolerant so as to facilitate stormwater retention and filtration.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring city plantings to be stormwater tolerant so as to facilitate stormwater retention and filtration.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the notification of schools concerning drug activity.
EventItemMatterName: Notification of schools concerning drug activity.
